[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1H pass 2C pass 2H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c49483f490b57eb655b46cc352587da34d66e4f79a7b379d85298f27ac88e9a6"]
[Category "Defense"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "defense/opening_leads"]
[Student "W"]
{The bidding has been as shown. The contract is 4\H 

Lead the \SK, the top of a 2-card honor sequence.

Against a suit contract you want to try to set up a quick winner in the suit.

Notice that with any other lead declarer would have been able to discard a \S loser  (maybe both of them) on dummy's \Cs.}
[Play "W"]SK

